
### ðŸ”Ž **Persistence via Registry Run Keys (Sysmon Event ID 13 â€” Registry Value Set)**

```spl
index=win_logs sourcetype="XmlWinEventLog:Microsoft-Windows-Sysmon/Operational" EventCode=13
| search TargetObject="*\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Run\\*"
```

---

### ðŸ”Ž **Optional: include both Current User & Local Machine keys**

```spl
index=win_logs sourcetype="XmlWinEventLog:Microsoft-Windows-Sysmon/Operational" EventCode=13
(TargetObject="*\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Run\\*" OR TargetObject="*\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\RunOnce\\*")
```

---

### ðŸ”Ž **To see exact command written into the registry**

```spl
index=win_logs sourcetype="XmlWinEventLog:Microsoft-Windows-Sysmon/Operational" EventCode=13
(TargetObject="*\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Run\\*" OR TargetObject="*\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\RunOnce\\*")
| table _time ComputerName UserName TargetObject Details
```

---

âœ… **Explanation:**

* `EventCode=13` â€” Sysmon logs any registry key value set.
* `TargetObject` â€” shows which registry key was modified.
* `Details` â€” shows the value written (typically the persistence payload).
